======================================================================
SYNTHESIS: THE DETERMINANTAL FORMULA FOR H
======================================================================

WHAT WE FOUND:

1. The Q_k spectrum determines H (for circulant tournaments)
2. det(aI + diag(Q)) = a^m B_m(1/a) — parametric identity
3. det(I + diag(Q)) = F_p — Fibonacci
4. The Cassini identity is det([[B_m, B_{m-1}],[B_{m+1}, B_m]]) = -x
5. H/p does NOT equal any simple determinant of diag(Q)
6. H/p is NOT perm of a simple Fibonacci matrix
7. The Hankel determinant of Q-moments = Vandermonde² (classical)

KEY INSIGHT: H depends on MORE than just the Q_k.
H depends on the PHASES of the eigenvalues λ_k = -1/2 + i·D_k
where D_k = Σ σ_i sin(2πk·a_i/p).
The Q_k = 1/4 + D_k² lose the phase information.

For the Interval tournament, the phases are FIXED (all σ_i = +1).
So the eigenvalues λ_k = -1/2 + i·D_k(+1,...,+1) are determined
by the FULL eigenvalue spectrum, not just Q_k = |λ_k|².

CONCLUSION: To express H as a determinant, we need a matrix
built from the FULL eigenvalues λ_k (including phases), not just Q_k.

det(zI - Λ) where Λ = diag(λ_1,...,λ_{p-1}) at z = ??? gives H?

